= 100 EPO Counterparts Found for IBM's 500 "Freed" US Patents =
->
[ [:IbmEp0501De: deutsch]
]
[ [:Ibm0501En: IBM Frees Patents]
| [http://www.ibm.com/ibm/licensing/patents/pledgedpatents.pdf Original List]
| [http://swpat.ffii.org/patents/samples/ep767419/ EP 767419]
| [http://gauss.ffii.org/ Database]
| [:SwpatcninoEn: Patent News]
]
----

In a preliminary investigation, FFII has found a match of 98 european patents in the portfolio of the 500 US patents IBM has decided to be royalty free for Open Source developers and companies.

Most if not all of the identified EPO patents cover calculation rules claimed in terms of general-purpose computing equipment (computer-implemented solutions = software per se) and are therefore of little value both under the [http://swpat.ffii.org/analysis/epc52/ existing law] and under the [http://swpat.ffii.org/papers/europarl0309/ software patent directive as amended by the European Parliament in September 2003].  They would however be fully legalised by the [http://swpat.ffii.org/papers/europarl0309/cons0401/ Council's proposed version], for which IBM's patent department is [http://swpat.ffii.org/players/ibm/ heavily lobbying the EU].

== Details ==

From a preliminary investigation, using the [http://gauss.ffii.org/ Gauss Project Database] and standard SQL, FFII has found a match of 98 european patents in IBM's portfolio of 500 US patents: '''44''' granted, '''43''' withdrawn and '''11''' pending.

See the [http://gauss.ffii.org/View/EP795823/Comments comments on EP795823] for an overview of reasons why a patent application may have been withdrawn.

The database used contains mainly patents from e.g. G and H classes up till summer 2003. The investigation is therefore not complete.
Feedback systems for users of Gauss are under development. Guests are welcome to contribute on the [http://gauss.ffii.org/GaussGuest Gauss Project Wiki].

The original list of the 500 IBM patents can be found [http://www.ibm.com/ibm/licensing/patents/pledgedpatents.pdf here].

